<seg id="2990">To start with & kuser; it is sufficient to read the chapter Adaption of & kuser; to read.</seg>
<seg id="2991">After you have made changes, you need to save it. either use the appropriate icon of the toolbar or the Save file in the File menu.</seg>
<seg id="2992">& kuser; is a simple application. the main window consists of two flashcards, the user and the user group list. for editing, select the desired user or group by double-clicking on the entry. it appears the dialog user and group properties.</seg>
<seg id="2993">Some flashcards are displayed only if you have set advanced system settings. only if you have activated space restrictions (Quota) for users, a card card is created on which you can make individual settings. other flashcards appear, if Shadow passwords or for example / etc / master.passwd are installed as in BSD-Unixes.</seg>
<seg id="2994">The password management card menu appears, if Shadow passwords or for example / etc / master.passwd are installed as in BSD-Unixes.</seg>
<seg id="2995">This card only appears if a filesystem space limitation (quota) is activated and initialized (recognizable at the file quota.user / quota.group on the file system).</seg>
<seg id="2996">These parameters can be individually set for each file system. the current file system is selected using the field file system with wildcard restriction.</seg>
<seg id="2997">The Groups tab informs about the group affiliations of the selected user. the default group to which the user belongs, you will find in the Primary group field. furthermore, the user can become a member in other groups by selecting them in the large field.</seg>
<seg id="2998">The batch dialog features a list of all users. to add a user to the group, mark this user on the list.</seg>
<seg id="2999">To add a user or group, select Add from the User or Group menu or click the appropriate Add button on the toolbar. editing or deleting the selected user respectively the selected group works analogously.</seg>
